"{\"value\":{\"mdx\":\"# Builder Codes\\n\\nBuilder codes enables external parties to submit orders to dYdX and collect fees (per-order) for building and routing an order to the exchange.\\nThe address and fee, in parts per million, needs to be configured via the `BuilderCodeParameters` in the order message itself. The fee will be paid out when the given order is filled.\\n\\nBuilder fees and addresses can be queried via the indexer using the `/orders` and `/fills` endpoints as usual. `/orders` contains details on the fee rate and builder address. `/fills` also contains the builder address as well as details on the amount charged per-fill.\\n\\n\\n## Changes To The Order Message\\n\\n::::steps\\n\\n## BuilderCodeParameters\\n`BuilderCodeParameters` is an addition to the order message which will specify:\\n    - `partner address` - where fees will be routed\\n    - `fee (in ppm)` that will be charged on order matching\\n\\n```go\\nmessage Order {\\n  // The unique ID of this order. Meant to be unique across all orders.\\n  OrderId order_id = 1 [ (gogoproto.nullable) = false ];\\n\\t\\n\\t...\\n\\t\\n\\t// builder_code is the metadata for the partner or builder of an order.\\n  BuilderCodeParameters builder_code_params = 12;\\n}\\n\\n// BuilderCodeParameters represents the metadata for the \\n// partner or builder of an order. This allows them to \\n// specify a fee for providing there service\\n// which will be paid out in the event of an order fill.\\nmessage BuilderCodeParameters {\\n  // The address of the builder to which the fee will be paid.\\n  string builder_address = 1;\\n\\n  // The fee enforced on the order in ppm.\\n  uint32 fee_ppm = 2;\\n}\\n```\\n\\n:::note\\n`BuilderCodeParameters` is an optional field\\n:::\\n\\n## Order Validation Checks\\n    - Ensure the `builder address` is valid\\n    - Ensure the `feePPM` is in the range `(0, 10,000]`\\n\\n::::\",\"document\":[{\"href\":\"/interaction/integration/integration-builder-codes#builder-codes\",\"html\":\"</header>\\n<p>Builder codes enables external parties to submit orders to dYdX and collect fees (per-order) for building and routing an order to the exchange.\\nThe address and fee, in parts per million, needs to be configured via the <code>BuilderCodeParameters</code> in the order message itself. The fee will be paid out when the given order is filled.</p>\\n<p>Builder fees and addresses can be queried via the indexer using the <code>/orders</code> and <code>/fills</code> endpoints as usual. <code>/orders</code> contains details on the fee rate and builder address. <code>/fills</code> also contains the builder address as well as details on the amount charged per-fill.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/integration/integration-builder-codes.mdx#builder-codes\",\"isPage\":true,\"text\":\"\\nBuilder codes enables external parties to submit orders to dYdX and collect fees (per-order) for building and routing an order to the exchange.\\nThe address and fee, in parts per million, needs to be configured via the BuilderCodeParameters in the order message itself. The fee will be paid out when the given order is filled.\\nBuilder fees and addresses can be queried via the indexer using the /orders and /fills endpoints as usual. /orders contains details on the fee rate and builder address. /fills also contains the builder address as well as details on the amount charged per-fill.\\n\",\"title\":\"Builder Codes\",\"titles\":[]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/integration/integration-builder-codes#changes-to-the-order-message\",\"html\":\"\\n<div data-vocs-steps=\\\"true\\\"><div data-depth=\\\"2\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/integration/integration-builder-codes.mdx#changes-to-the-order-message\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\",\"title\":\"Changes To The Order Message\",\"titles\":[\"Builder Codes\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/integration/integration-builder-codes#buildercodeparameters\",\"html\":\"<p><code>BuilderCodeParameters</code> is an addition to the order message which will specify:</p><ul>\\n<li><code>partner address</code> - where fees will be routed</li>\\n<li><code>fee (in ppm)</code> that will be charged on order matching</li>\\n</ul><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">message Order {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">  // The unique ID of this order. Meant to be unique across all orders.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">  OrderId order_id </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> 1</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> [ (gogoproto.nullable) </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> false</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> ];</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">\\t</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">\\t...</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">\\t</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">\\t// builder_code is the metadata for the partner or builder of an order.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">  BuilderCodeParameters builder_code_params </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> 12</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">;</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">}</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\" data-empty-line=\\\"true\\\"> </span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">// BuilderCodeParameters represents the metadata for the </span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">// partner or builder of an order. This allows them to </span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">// specify a fee for providing there service</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">// which will be paid out in the event of an order fill.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">message BuilderCodeParameters {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">  // The address of the builder to which the fee will be paid.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">  string</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> builder_address </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> 1</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">;</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\" data-empty-line=\\\"true\\\"> </span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\">  // The fee enforced on the order in ppm.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">  uint32</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> fee_ppm </span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> 2</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">;</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">}</span></span></code></pre><aside data-callout=\\\"note\\\"><p><code>BuilderCodeParameters</code> is an optional field</p></aside></div><div data-depth=\\\"2\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/integration/integration-builder-codes.mdx#buildercodeparameters\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"BuilderCodeParameters is an addition to the order message which will specify:\\npartner address - where fees will be routed\\nfee (in ppm) that will be charged on order matching\\nmessage Order {\\n  // The unique ID of this order. Meant to be unique across all orders.\\n  OrderId order_id = 1 [ (gogoproto.nullable) = false ];\\n\\t\\n\\t...\\n\\t\\n\\t// builder_code is the metadata for the partner or builder of an order.\\n  BuilderCodeParameters builder_code_params = 12;\\n}\\n \\n// BuilderCodeParameters represents the metadata for the \\n// partner or builder of an order. This allows them to \\n// specify a fee for providing there service\\n// which will be paid out in the event of an order fill.\\nmessage BuilderCodeParameters {\\n  // The address of the builder to which the fee will be paid.\\n  string builder_address = 1;\\n \\n  // The fee enforced on the order in ppm.\\n  uint32 fee_ppm = 2;\\n}BuilderCodeParameters is an optional field\",\"title\":\"BuilderCodeParameters\",\"titles\":[\"Builder Codes\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/integration/integration-builder-codes#order-validation-checks\",\"html\":\"<ul>\\n<li>Ensure the <code>builder address</code> is valid</li>\\n<li>Ensure the <code>feePPM</code> is in the range <code>(0, 10,000]</code></li>\\n</ul></div></div>\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/integration/integration-builder-codes.mdx#order-validation-checks\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nEnsure the builder address is valid\\nEnsure the feePPM is in the range (0, 10,000]\\n\",\"title\":\"Order Validation Checks\",\"titles\":[\"Builder Codes\"]}]}}"
